#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/index.md:17
msgid ""
"The custom configuration created by the developers of NvChad allows you to "
"have an integrated environment with many of the features of a graphical IDE. "
"These features are built into the Neovim configuration by means of plugins. "
"Those selected for NvChad by the developers have the function of setting up "
"the editor for general use."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/index.md:19
msgid ""
"However, the ecosystem of plugins for Neovim is much broader and through "
"their use, allows you to extend the editor to focus on your own needs."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/index.md:21
msgid ""
"The scenario addressed in this section is the creation of documentation for "
"Rocky Linux, so plugins for writing Markdown code, managing Git "
"repositories, and other tasks that relate to the purpose will be explained."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/index.md:22
#, no-wrap
msgid "Requirements"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/index.md:27
msgid ""
"- NvChad properly installed on the system with the \"*template chadrc*\" - "
"Familiarity with the command line - An active internet connection"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/index.md:28
#, no-wrap
msgid "General hints about plugins"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/index.md:31
msgid ""
"If you chose during the installation of NvChad to also install the [template "
"chadrc](../template_chadrc.md) you will have in your configuration a **~/."
"config/nvim/lua/custom/** folder. All changes for your plugins should be "
"made in the **/custom/plugins.lua** file in that folder. In case the plugin "
"needs additional configurations, these are placed in the **/custom/configs** "
"folder."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/index.md:33
msgid ""
"Neovim, on which the configuration of NvChad is based, does not integrate an "
"automatic configuration update mechanism with the running editor. This "
"implies that each time the plugins file is modified, it is necessary to stop "
"`nvim` and then reopen it to get the full functionality of the plugin."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/index.md:35
msgid ""
"Installation of the plugin can be performed immediately after it is placed "
"in the file since the `lazy.nvim` plugins manager keeps track of the changes "
"in **plugins.lua** and therefore allows its \"live\" installation."
msgstr ""

